%% Feast Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4-ea.1/feast.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>redhat-ods-applications
    participant Deploy as Feast Deployment<br/>(online/offline/registry/UI)
    participant Git as Git Repository<br/>443/TCP HTTPS (optional)
    participant DB as Database Backend<br/>(PostgreSQL/Redis/etc.)
    participant ObjStore as Object Storage<br/>(S3/GCS)

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 1: FeatureStore Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (FeatureStore)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Services,<br/>ConfigMaps, PVCs, RBAC, Routes<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Deploy: Schedule pods
    Deploy->>Git: feast init (clone project)<br/>Auth: User-configured (optional)
    Deploy->>DB: Connect to persistence backend<br/>Auth: User-configured (optional)

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 2: Feature Serving (Online Store)
    participant MLApp as ML Application
    MLApp->>Deploy: GET/POST feast-{name}-online<br/>Port: 80/TCP or 443/TCP<br/>Encryption: TLS (OCP auto)<br/>Auth: K8s RBAC / OIDC (optional)
    Deploy->>DB: Query features<br/>Auth: User-configured
    DB-->>Deploy: Feature values
    Deploy-->>MLApp: Feature response

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 3: CronJob Materialization
    participant CronJob as CronJob Pod<br/>(ose-cli)
    CronJob->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec into Feast pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Deploy: exec: feast apply +<br/>feast materialize-incremental
    Deploy->>DB: Write materialized features
    DB-->>Deploy: Confirmation

    Note over User,ObjStore: Flow 4: Notebook Feast Integration
    participant Notebook as Kubeflow Notebook
    User->>K8sAPI: Label Notebook with<br/>opendatahub.io/feast-integration=true
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (Notebook CR)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Read FeatureStore client ConfigMaps
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create {notebook}-feast-config<br/>ConfigMap
    Notebook->>Deploy: Use feast client config<br/>to access feature store
